MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2003-0996. O’Connor v. Wolff.

This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of prohibition. Upon consideration of relator’s application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the application for dismissal be, and hereby is, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.

Rupert A. Doan, J., of the First Appellate District, sitting for Moyer, C. J.
